2
00:01:07.551 --> 00:01:12.071
(Doom at Your Service)

3
00:01:12.331 --> 00:01:15.242
(All characters. locations. organizations. religions.)

4
00:01:15.327 --> 00:01:17.951
(and incidents in this drama are fictional.)

5
00:01:18.817 --> 00:01:21.617
(Episode 6)

6
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:28.311
Love me.

7
00:01:35.621 --> 00:01:37.121
Love me if you can.

8
00:01:39.350 --> 00:01:41.661
That wouldn't be such a bad idea either.

9
00:01:41.890 --> 00:01:42.990
So...

10
00:01:45.261 --> 00:01:47.201
be the first human to love me.

11
00:01:55.371 --> 00:01:56.600
So...

12
00:01:58.871 --> 00:02:00.040
what do you mean by that?

13
00:02:00.040 --> 00:02:02.911
When you tried to save me. you said you just wanted to.

14
00:02:03.180 --> 00:02:05.311
So you told me to just thank you.

15
00:02:06.110 --> 00:02:08.280
This is my way of thanking you.

16
00:02:09.181 --> 00:02:10.720
You just want to die.

17
00:02:10.720 --> 00:02:12.121
I want to save you.

18
00:02:13.791 --> 00:02:15.321
You don't mean that.

19
00:02:15.321 --> 00:02:17.130
How can my offer be bad for you?

20
00:02:17.431 --> 00:02:18.561
Yes. it can.

21
00:02:19.291 --> 00:02:22.360
It's ruining my mood. It puts me in a bad mood.

22
00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:24.871
Does your feeling matter more than staying alive?

23
00:02:27.241 --> 00:02:28.800
You don't know how you look...

24
00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:30.341
when you look at things that disappear. right?

25
00:02:31.640 --> 00:02:33.440
I know that face because I see that every day.

26
00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:36.640
When I look at you looking at me.

27
00:02:36.841 --> 00:02:38.481
I can see right through you.

28
00:02:42.050 --> 00:02:44.291
- See what? - That you're a good guy.

29
00:02:48.190 --> 00:02:49.991
Staying alive isn't what I want.

30
00:02:50.390 --> 00:02:52.231
I want to live a happy life.

31
00:02:53.330 --> 00:02:54.961
And I just realized that.

32
00:02:56.461 --> 00:02:58.101
That's how I came to this conclusion.

33
00:03:01.300 --> 00:03:02.371
I...

34
00:03:07.511 --> 00:03:10.081
don't think I can be happy after making you disappear.

35
00:03:20.891 --> 00:03:22.260
So don't get cheeky with me.

36
00:03:32.570 --> 00:03:34.371
I apologize for any concerns I have caused.

37
00:03:34.700 --> 00:03:36.171
I will cooperate to the best of my abilities.

38
00:03:36.171 --> 00:03:37.410
I can fall in love.

39
00:03:38.241 --> 00:03:39.811
I can fall in love.

40
00:03:40.171 --> 00:03:42.081
- What are you doing? - Mind your business.

41
00:03:42.241 --> 00:03:43.611
I can fall in love.

42
00:03:44.211 --> 00:03:45.510
I can fall...

43
00:03:45.510 --> 00:03:47.181
You're making that hard.

44
00:03:47.181 --> 00:03:48.181
in love.

45
00:03:48.181 --> 00:03:49.780
What? No. I can't. What?

46
00:03:51.450 --> 00:03:52.621
Darn it.

47
00:03:53.621 --> 00:03:54.690
You sure are trying hard.

48
00:03:54.690 --> 00:03:58.331
("The CEO of Kanghan Pharmaceuticals Gets Arrested for Embezzlement")

49
00:03:58.831 --> 00:03:59.831
This won't work.

50
00:04:04.470 --> 00:04:07.271
Starting tonight. I'm going to sleep alone in my room.

51
00:04:07.271 --> 00:04:09.801
- Why? - To detach myself from you.

52
00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:17.410
Let's sleep together.

53
00:04:20.651 --> 00:04:22.551
Sleep with me.

54
00:04:27.151 --> 00:04:29.491
Hey. stop acting.

55
00:04:30.961 --> 00:04:32.130
You got me.

56
00:04:36.401 --> 00:04:37.431
Darn you.

57
00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:41.371
When you go into your room. I should do something to your house.

58
00:04:42.070 --> 00:04:43.141
Hey!

59
00:04:46.570 --> 00:04:47.811
Gosh.

60
00:04:56.720 --> 00:04:58.991
I'm sleeping here because I'm concerned...

61
00:04:58.991 --> 00:05:00.290
that you might do something to my house.

62
00:05:02.491 --> 00:05:03.491
Okay.

63
00:05:04.061 --> 00:05:05.290
I'm serious.

64
00:05:06.190 --> 00:05:07.190
Sure.

65
00:05:10.431 --> 00:05:12.100
Do you even know what it means to love someone?

66
00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:14.000
Why do you keep telling me to love you?

67
00:05:14.700 --> 00:05:17.340
Since I don't know what love is. I'm telling you to love me.

68
00:05:19.871 --> 00:05:21.080
Forget it.

69
00:05:26.250 --> 00:05:27.320
Love me.

70
00:05:29.551 --> 00:05:30.851
Then. I'll die for you.

71
00:05:40.830 --> 00:05:41.861
Good night.

72
00:06:00.650 --> 00:06:04.020
(Mister)

73
00:06:04.551 --> 00:06:06.921
How can she name me Human when I'm not even human?

74
00:06:07.390 --> 00:06:08.760
She's so weird.

75
00:06:09.291 --> 00:06:10.621
How suitable.

76
00:06:10.960 --> 00:06:12.861
- The name? - The girl.

77
00:06:14.630 --> 00:06:16.700
A weirdo met another weirdo.

78
00:06:16.931 --> 00:06:19.171
You created her and are calling her weird.

79
00:06:19.330 --> 00:06:22.041
To be named. there must be people who would need to call you.

80
00:06:22.601 --> 00:06:24.340
And now. you got someone who would call for you.

81
00:06:24.340 --> 00:06:26.871
- I didn't ask for it. - Yes. you did.

82
00:06:27.840 --> 00:06:29.640
You always did like a little kid.

83
00:06:33.880 --> 00:06:36.080
So will you disappear?

84
00:06:39.551 --> 00:06:40.551
What...

85
00:06:40.551 --> 00:06:43.890
Wasn't that your plan? After getting her to love you?

86
00:06:46.791 --> 00:06:48.260
"The deities know everything."

87
00:06:50.700 --> 00:06:52.101
"They just pretend to be clueless."

88
00:06:53.330 --> 00:06:55.140
Will it go as you planned?

89
00:06:55.140 --> 00:06:56.301
(50 cents)

90
00:06:56.900 --> 00:06:58.041
What do you mean?

91
00:07:05.851 --> 00:07:07.950
Love can be more dangerous than you think.

92
00:07:08.150 --> 00:07:10.750
To protect their loved ones. they can throw away the world.

93
00:07:12.090 --> 00:07:13.950
You don't know how it will turn out.

94
00:07:14.561 --> 00:07:16.090
And I always find that fun.

95
00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:25.971
Did you see the new part-timer at the cafe?

96
00:07:25.971 --> 00:07:28.640
Since he's new. I see a new kind of hotness.

97
00:07:28.640 --> 00:07:30.340
Hey. can you set me up with someone?

98
00:07:31.041 --> 00:07:33.510
Hey. I saw him for the first time on my way to work.

99
00:07:33.510 --> 00:07:35.080
Not that part-timer.

100
00:07:35.411 --> 00:07:37.650
Do you know any guys who deserve to die?

101
00:07:37.650 --> 00:07:39.281
If you do. can you introduce me to them?

102
00:07:39.510 --> 00:07:40.981
You don't know what you're asking.

103
00:07:40.981 --> 00:07:42.551
Why would I set you up with losers?

104
00:07:42.551 --> 00:07:44.590
Exactly. Introduce me to losers.

105
00:07:44.991 --> 00:07:46.150
I'll handle them.

106
00:07:46.150 --> 00:07:47.791
How will you handle them?

107
00:07:47.791 --> 00:07:49.991
Nicely to perfection.

108
00:07:49.991 --> 00:07:53.190
I'll get rid of them as if they never existed here.

109
00:07:53.190 --> 00:07:54.231
Are you in a cleanup crew?

110
00:07:54.431 --> 00:07:55.931
Should I set you up with Mr. Park?

111
00:07:55.931 --> 00:07:59.000
Oh. right. I forgot about the CEO.

112
00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:00.171
Unbelievable.

113
00:08:00.171 --> 00:08:01.601
Are you that stressed out?

114
00:08:01.601 --> 00:08:03.101
Do you have to end a guy?

115
00:08:03.601 --> 00:08:05.671
Let's look at this hot guy and calm down.

116
00:08:06.270 --> 00:08:07.440
Let's go.

117
00:08:12.181 --> 00:08:13.181
Hello.

118
00:08:16.020 --> 00:08:17.020
Dong Kyung.

119
00:08:18.320 --> 00:08:19.351
"Dong Kyung"?

120
00:08:21.390 --> 00:08:22.390
Well...

121
00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:31.330
You should quit your job first.

122
00:08:32.070 --> 00:08:33.070
Why?

123
00:08:33.900 --> 00:08:35.301
I'll take care of everything.

124
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.041
Take care of what?

125
00:08:38.611 --> 00:08:39.871
Making money.

126
00:08:44.411 --> 00:08:45.450
Sun Kyung.

127
00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:50.520
What?

128
00:08:53.090 --> 00:08:56.791
It's so odd. you know. It wasn't fun at all.

129
00:08:57.991 --> 00:09:00.390
At times. I really didn't want to do it.

130
00:09:00.531 --> 00:09:02.101
But now that...

131
00:09:02.101 --> 00:09:04.301
I will have to quit not because I want to.

132
00:09:04.700 --> 00:09:07.000
I strangely want to keep working.

133
00:09:08.671 --> 00:09:10.171
Come to think of it.

134
00:09:10.471 --> 00:09:13.541
this was the longest job I had in my life.

135
00:09:15.080 --> 00:09:16.181
So...

136
00:09:17.281 --> 00:09:20.281
don't steal my last six years of my life.

137
00:09:21.380 --> 00:09:23.880
I already started to feel how precious my time is.

138
00:09:28.061 --> 00:09:29.090
Sorry.

139
00:09:30.421 --> 00:09:33.190
I'm sorry for all the mean things I said. the lies I told you.

140
00:09:33.761 --> 00:09:35.700
and wasting your life. I'm sorry for everything.

141
00:09:38.330 --> 00:09:39.370
Sorry.

142
00:09:42.401 --> 00:09:45.470
Hey. that doesn't suit you. Don't be so apologetic.

143
00:09:45.771 --> 00:09:47.011
Right back at you.

144
00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:50.141
Don't sound like you're counting the days until you die.

145
00:09:50.511 --> 00:09:51.911
Don't give up.

146
00:09:55.181 --> 00:09:56.320
This is so annoying.

147
00:09:58.921 --> 00:10:01.590
Go. I need to go back to work.

148
00:10:02.791 --> 00:10:04.021
I'm working too.

149
00:10:06.073 --> 00:10:07.203
Good luck.

150
00:10:09.073 --> 00:10:10.142
You too.

151
00:10:11.482 --> 00:10:14.583
Sure. I'll do my best too...

152
00:10:15.453 --> 00:10:16.482
at everything.

153
00:10:17.622 --> 00:10:20.183
Is that really what I said?

154
00:10:20.723 --> 00:10:22.193
I can't reach Young Prince.

155
00:10:23.553 --> 00:10:24.963
I take it back.

156
00:10:25.362 --> 00:10:26.862
I was talking nonsense.

157
00:10:27.732 --> 00:10:29.732
His mom acts like she doesn't know anything either.

158
00:10:29.732 --> 00:10:32.163
She keeps telling me she doesn't know where her son is.

159
00:10:33.402 --> 00:10:35.602
Did he say anything to you the last time you met him?

160
00:10:35.602 --> 00:10:36.973
No. not really.

161
00:10:37.433 --> 00:10:40.973
We already uploaded a post about his upcoming novel.

162
00:10:43.473 --> 00:10:46.683
Yes. I know that.

163
00:10:46.683 --> 00:10:48.482
Do everything you can to bring him back.

164
00:10:48.482 --> 00:10:49.713
That's our only solution.

165
00:10:52.323 --> 00:10:53.982
This is so annoying.

166
00:10:55.223 --> 00:10:56.752
You're not talking about me. are you?

167
00:10:56.752 --> 00:10:58.492
Everything is so annoying.

168
00:11:02.213 --> 00:11:03.244
But not me. right?

169
00:11:04.313 --> 00:11:05.884
These darn writers...

170
00:11:07.313 --> 00:11:09.254
are so ungrateful.

171
00:11:10.124 --> 00:11:13.193
I should gather them and make them dig holes for no reason.

172
00:11:16.223 --> 00:11:18.833
All they ever do is write novels.

173
00:11:18.833 --> 00:11:20.904
But just because we're so submissive.

174
00:11:20.904 --> 00:11:22.733
they become so full of themselves.

175
00:11:22.733 --> 00:11:24.803
Everyone looks down on me...

176
00:11:24.803 --> 00:11:27.233
including the kids!

177
00:11:27.874 --> 00:11:29.544
Darn it.

178
00:11:29.703 --> 00:11:31.374
You're starting to make me feel guilty.

179
00:11:33.544 --> 00:11:35.183
I mean. how could he suddenly go MIA...

180
00:11:35.183 --> 00:11:38.713
a week before the main event of his upcoming novel?

181
00:11:38.713 --> 00:11:40.313
- My gosh. - What?

182
00:11:40.884 --> 00:11:42.884
You should've given me the opportunity instead.

183
00:11:44.994 --> 00:11:47.294
I guess you have to be a little nuts to be a good writer.

184
00:11:47.864 --> 00:11:49.264
Do you think I'm too normal?

185
00:11:50.323 --> 00:11:51.394
You are...

186
00:11:52.864 --> 00:11:55.963
one of the few sane writers.

187
00:11:56.864 --> 00:11:58.634
That's why I love you.

188
00:11:59.933 --> 00:12:02.573
Should I just love that little punk?

189
00:12:02.874 --> 00:12:05.713
No. the age gap is just too big...

190
00:12:05.713 --> 00:12:06.774
for me to love him.

191
00:12:07.744 --> 00:12:10.114
Stop leaving out the subject and object of your sentence.

192
00:12:10.114 --> 00:12:12.083
I can't seem to follow because you're all over the place.

193
00:12:12.353 --> 00:12:14.254
Ji Na. do you happen to know any horrible guys...

194
00:12:14.254 --> 00:12:16.124
you want to kill?

195
00:12:16.583 --> 00:12:17.654
What if I do?

196
00:12:18.323 --> 00:12:19.353
Introduce me to him.

197
00:12:19.424 --> 00:12:20.754
Should I introduce you to Hyun Kyu?

198
00:12:21.424 --> 00:12:24.024
Should I kill him for you?

199
00:12:24.433 --> 00:12:25.463
Hey.

200
00:12:26.494 --> 00:12:27.904
I'm kidding.

201
00:12:27.904 --> 00:12:30.034
You said you're going to go to the school reunion.

202
00:12:31.904 --> 00:12:34.274
I thought you planned to kill him yourself.

203
00:12:35.803 --> 00:12:37.404
That was the plan.

204
00:12:38.914 --> 00:12:40.114
But?

205
00:12:41.213 --> 00:12:42.443
But someone told me...

206
00:12:42.914 --> 00:12:45.583
that what I'm doing isn't revenge but a struggle to get over him.

207
00:12:46.583 --> 00:12:48.624
Who told you that? Mr. Cha?

208
00:12:50.654 --> 00:12:51.823
How did you know?

209
00:12:54.223 --> 00:12:57.264
Ji Na. about Mr. Cha...

210
00:13:03.463 --> 00:13:05.274
He apparently pitied you back then.

211
00:13:05.274 --> 00:13:07.103
That's why he kissed you.

212
00:13:11.144 --> 00:13:12.213
What?

213
00:13:14.583 --> 00:13:16.784
- How's work? - It's going well.

214
00:13:17.514 --> 00:13:18.754
Goodness.

215
00:13:19.754 --> 00:13:21.754
I know you're just saying that.

216
00:13:22.683 --> 00:13:24.823
I heard the cafe on the first floor is doing very well.

217
00:13:24.823 --> 00:13:27.024
I recognized Hyun Kyu the moment I saw him.

218
00:13:27.124 --> 00:13:30.093
He has what it takes to run a business.

219
00:13:30.164 --> 00:13:33.433
The company you work for is my biggest worry in that building.

220
00:13:33.693 --> 00:13:36.433
I can easily tell that the CEO is an idler.

221
00:13:36.433 --> 00:13:37.904
How is he going to afford to pay the rent?

222
00:13:37.904 --> 00:13:39.103
You get your rent every month.

223
00:13:39.103 --> 00:13:41.504
That's because I do a good job of managing your building.

224
00:13:41.504 --> 00:13:43.343
That company won't last long.

225
00:13:43.343 --> 00:13:46.044
I've seen many different tenants for dozens of years.

226
00:13:46.213 --> 00:13:47.943
The fact that you're here eating steak with me...

227
00:13:47.943 --> 00:13:49.313
instead of working overtime...

228
00:13:49.313 --> 00:13:51.914
Hasn't it occurred to you that I made time to be with you?

229
00:13:51.914 --> 00:13:53.914
Your brother is so busy managing my buildings...

230
00:13:53.914 --> 00:13:55.154
that it's hard to even meet him.

231
00:13:55.154 --> 00:13:56.323
I'd rather prefer you do that.

232
00:13:56.323 --> 00:13:57.953
Then why don't you put me in charge...

233
00:13:57.953 --> 00:13:59.823
of a few more buildings. so I can become a lot busier?

234
00:14:00.853 --> 00:14:02.463
I'm not going to fall for that.

235
00:14:02.563 --> 00:14:04.894
Don't even think of slacking off just because I'm rich.

236
00:14:04.894 --> 00:14:06.563
I gave up on that dream when I was in kindergarten.

237
00:14:07.034 --> 00:14:09.864
You really do take after me. You never lose an argument.

238
00:14:09.864 --> 00:14:12.433
Dad. let's get this straight.

239
00:14:12.534 --> 00:14:14.303
My looks come from Mom.

240
00:14:18.874 --> 00:14:21.583
Are you seeing anyone?

241
00:14:22.114 --> 00:14:24.213
You're a handsome fellow thanks to your mother.

242
00:14:24.213 --> 00:14:25.353
I'm seeing a lot of women.

243
00:14:25.353 --> 00:14:27.213
Really? How many?

244
00:14:28.124 --> 00:14:30.124
Well. about 30.

245
00:14:30.124 --> 00:14:31.394
You darn punk.

246
00:14:31.394 --> 00:14:33.524
Hearing you call me that tells me it's time for me to leave.

247
00:14:33.754 --> 00:14:36.264
I'm done with my briefing and dinner. so I'll go now.

248
00:14:36.264 --> 00:14:37.524
I stayed for too long.

249
00:14:40.193 --> 00:14:43.134
A man should be responsible for his actions.

250
00:14:43.134 --> 00:14:45.174
The same goes for women. you punk.

251
00:14:47.803 --> 00:14:49.443
That's what I'm doing right now.

252
00:14:49.443 --> 00:14:50.573
(Na Ji Na)

253
00:14:51.244 --> 00:14:53.174
- Hello? - Do you pity me?

254
00:14:54.683 --> 00:14:56.683
I asked you if you pity me.

255
00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:58.313
Yes. I pitied you back then.

256
00:14:58.813 --> 00:14:59.953
But not anymore.

257
00:15:01.124 --> 00:15:02.424
Did you eat dinner?

258
00:15:02.424 --> 00:15:04.053
That's the last thing you should be worried about.

259
00:15:04.223 --> 00:15:05.693
Then let's just say you ate.

260
00:15:07.024 --> 00:15:08.093
Why did you want to meet?

261
00:15:08.093 --> 00:15:10.463
I'm sure it wasn't because you wanted to argue about this.

262
00:15:10.463 --> 00:15:12.563
- Actually. that's exactly why. - Then we should go.

263
00:15:12.563 --> 00:15:15.364
Did you also offer to sign a deal because you pitied me?

264
00:15:15.634 --> 00:15:17.364
Do I seem like a person who'd do that?

265
00:15:18.534 --> 00:15:19.573
No. it's not that...

266
00:15:19.573 --> 00:15:22.343
Then do you doubt my judgment regarding your competence?

267
00:15:23.004 --> 00:15:25.144
Or do you just think you're not that good of a writer?

268
00:15:31.884 --> 00:15:33.083
(Hyun Kyu)

269
00:15:41.124 --> 00:15:42.394
(Hyun Kyu)

270
00:15:45.134 --> 00:15:46.733
It's okay. You can take the call.

271
00:15:51.203 --> 00:15:52.473
- Hey. - Why didn't you pick up?

272
00:15:52.473 --> 00:15:53.504
What are you doing right now?

273
00:15:53.504 --> 00:15:54.904
When are you coming home? I'm hungry.

274
00:15:54.904 --> 00:15:56.644
It's your turn to cook today.

275
00:15:56.774 --> 00:15:58.274
I'm working. I'll be late.

276
00:15:59.843 --> 00:16:01.614
Who's making you work until so late?

277
00:16:01.614 --> 00:16:03.213
What a jerk.

278
00:16:04.284 --> 00:16:06.014
You're the jerk.

279
00:16:07.284 --> 00:16:09.353
What? Me? Why?

280
00:16:09.483 --> 00:16:11.083
- Let's hang up. - Joo Ik!

281
00:16:14.593 --> 00:16:17.294
This guy's the person I pity.

282
00:16:18.164 --> 00:16:19.364
So what about the deal?

283
00:16:19.534 --> 00:16:21.264
Are you going to sign it or not?

284
00:16:26.103 --> 00:16:27.274
I signed it.

285
00:16:28.073 --> 00:16:29.144
You won't regret it.

286
00:16:29.644 --> 00:16:31.473
You sound like a con artist when you say that.

287
00:16:32.213 --> 00:16:33.414
I feel like I will.

288
00:16:33.414 --> 00:16:34.414
That won't be too bad either.

289
00:16:34.414 --> 00:16:36.144
I've seen you regret things several times anyway.

290
00:16:36.683 --> 00:16:38.284
You might not know it. but you don't look so bad...

291
00:16:38.284 --> 00:16:39.654
when you regret something.

292
00:16:41.884 --> 00:16:44.254
Next time. let's meet at your studio. I'll call you.

293
00:16:44.624 --> 00:16:45.853
I need to check my schedule...

294
00:16:45.853 --> 00:16:48.264
You agreed to comply with all of my demands.

295
00:16:48.264 --> 00:16:49.463
It's a done deal.

296
00:16:57.333 --> 00:16:59.233
Gosh. I'm so stupid.

297
00:16:59.833 --> 00:17:01.744
I got too convinced.

298
00:17:14.254 --> 00:17:17.254
Gosh. you startled me. What are you doing here?

299
00:17:17.424 --> 00:17:19.624
Did you find a jerk to kill so you can save your life?

300
00:17:21.424 --> 00:17:23.193
I'm looking for one. so don't worry.

301
00:17:23.323 --> 00:17:25.563
I can't help but worry.

302
00:17:26.933 --> 00:17:28.463
You're special to me.

303
00:17:35.144 --> 00:17:38.313
My gosh. Unbelievable.

304
00:17:39.274 --> 00:17:41.384
Look at you playing tricks again.

305
00:17:42.014 --> 00:17:44.183
I'm not playing tricks. I'm very sincere.

306
00:17:44.983 --> 00:17:48.853
At least bring me flowers to show that you mean it.

307
00:17:48.853 --> 00:17:50.683
Is that what I should've done?

308
00:17:51.154 --> 00:17:53.953
Seriously? Are you provoking me right now?

309
00:17:54.193 --> 00:17:55.693
Why are you angry? I'm trying to help you.

310
00:17:55.764 --> 00:17:59.063
You're not helping. You're getting in my way.

311
00:17:59.333 --> 00:18:00.933
Give me that. I'll carry it.

312
00:18:02.233 --> 00:18:04.773
Hey. I'm warning you.

313
00:18:04.773 --> 00:18:07.773
Stop being nice to me.

314
00:18:08.604 --> 00:18:09.674
Give it to me.

315
00:18:10.174 --> 00:18:12.473
Hey... Give me that.

316
00:18:12.614 --> 00:18:15.844
- My gosh. come on. - Looking nice. you guys.

317
00:18:15.983 --> 00:18:18.054
You guys look like a newlywed couple.

318
00:18:18.314 --> 00:18:19.384
Hey. Brother-in-law.

319
00:18:19.683 --> 00:18:22.054
- Hi. Brother-in-law. - Cut it out.

320
00:18:22.054 --> 00:18:24.384
What are you doing here all of a sudden?

321
00:18:24.384 --> 00:18:25.394
Me?

322
00:18:25.793 --> 00:18:26.993
I came to give you this.

323
00:18:27.654 --> 00:18:30.624
I got you bungeoppang. Have them while they're still warm.

324
00:18:31.124 --> 00:18:34.193
I saw them outside. and I was reminded of you.

325
00:18:34.933 --> 00:18:37.864
I bet you don't know this. Dong Kyung loves adzuki beans.

326
00:18:37.864 --> 00:18:41.574
She goes crazy over omegi rice cakes and bungeoppang.

327
00:18:42.374 --> 00:18:43.804
Oh. really?

328
00:18:44.104 --> 00:18:46.374
I thought she loved flowers.

329
00:18:46.374 --> 00:18:47.414
"Flowers"?

330
00:18:48.283 --> 00:18:50.243
Well. yes. She likes flowers too.

331
00:18:50.344 --> 00:18:52.483
She just likes getting a lot of stuff.

332
00:18:52.983 --> 00:18:55.183
Just keep buying her stuff to keep her happy.

333
00:18:56.324 --> 00:18:58.253
Hey. what's your schedule tomorrow?

334
00:18:58.453 --> 00:19:01.223
Me? I have work tomorrow. I start work in the afternoon.

335
00:19:02.493 --> 00:19:04.793
That's good. I need you to come somewhere with me.

336
00:19:04.894 --> 00:19:05.963
Where?

337
00:19:07.293 --> 00:19:08.763
I wasn't talking to you.

338
00:19:09.334 --> 00:19:10.404
Where?

339
00:19:12.203 --> 00:19:13.334
It won't take long.

340
00:19:13.334 --> 00:19:15.804
- Where to? - Where to?

341
00:19:20.243 --> 00:19:21.314
You'll find out.

342
00:19:22.243 --> 00:19:24.344
Why won't you tell me? Where are you guys going?

343
00:19:38.465 --> 00:19:41.004
- Can we talk outside? - Sure.

344
00:19:42.834 --> 00:19:45.274
I was worried it might be genetic.

345
00:19:45.274 --> 00:19:47.205
That was the first thing that came to my mind.

346
00:19:48.314 --> 00:19:50.574
I have him to rely on. but as for him.

347
00:19:51.915 --> 00:19:56.614
I got worried he might get sick after I die.

348
00:19:58.584 --> 00:19:59.655
I'm glad.

349
00:20:00.054 --> 00:20:02.594
It's nice to know you have something to cling to.

350
00:20:02.655 --> 00:20:03.895
"Cling to"?

351
00:20:04.764 --> 00:20:05.764
To what?

352
00:20:05.764 --> 00:20:07.794
Your life.

353
00:20:09.435 --> 00:20:12.804
Your brother called and begged me...

354
00:20:12.804 --> 00:20:14.534
to convince you.

355
00:20:14.534 --> 00:20:18.034
He begged me to save your life...

356
00:20:18.504 --> 00:20:20.375
and told me he can't live without you.

357
00:20:23.044 --> 00:20:24.175
Well. so...

358
00:20:25.584 --> 00:20:27.645
I was hallucinating.

359
00:20:28.415 --> 00:20:30.915
People would show up out of nowhere...

360
00:20:30.915 --> 00:20:31.925
and disappear.

361
00:20:34.854 --> 00:20:36.794
That's not what matters.

362
00:20:38.054 --> 00:20:40.294
I think it really weighed down on my heart...

363
00:20:40.995 --> 00:20:42.495
that I couldn't persuade you.

364
00:20:45.235 --> 00:20:48.274
That's why I'm taking back what I said.

365
00:20:50.705 --> 00:20:51.745
Get treated.

366
00:20:52.975 --> 00:20:56.114
Even if it's only for a year or a few months. live longer.

367
00:20:57.245 --> 00:20:58.284
Take this...

368
00:21:00.385 --> 00:21:01.614
whenever you're in pain.

369
00:21:02.084 --> 00:21:03.885
Take it and endure it.

370
00:21:04.354 --> 00:21:05.455
and think it over.

371
00:21:06.485 --> 00:21:07.725
I'll hope you'll agree.

372
00:21:10.254 --> 00:21:13.264
I really want to save your life.

373
00:21:13.995 --> 00:21:17.064
I don't want another editor working on my next story.

374
00:21:18.165 --> 00:21:20.834
You're the best at finding typos.

375
00:21:23.804 --> 00:21:29.274
(Tak Dong Kyung)

376
00:21:47.495 --> 00:21:50.594
(Condolences)

377
00:21:53.864 --> 00:21:55.274
Open this for me.

378
00:21:57.205 --> 00:21:58.745
Hey. which bus do I need to take...

379
00:21:58.745 --> 00:22:00.104
to get to Myeong-dong?

380
00:22:01.675 --> 00:22:03.475
Open it for me. I'm thirsty.

381
00:22:04.175 --> 00:22:05.185
Okay.

382
00:22:10.215 --> 00:22:11.254
Here.

383
00:22:14.725 --> 00:22:15.824
Right?

384
00:22:17.455 --> 00:22:18.465
What?

385
00:22:18.465 --> 00:22:20.465
From the bus stop.

386
00:22:23.165 --> 00:22:26.504
It's so cool. meeting you again like that.

387
00:22:32.604 --> 00:22:35.344
- Are you sick? - What do you have?

388
00:22:35.844 --> 00:22:37.175
What? Me?

389
00:22:37.175 --> 00:22:39.185
You must be here because you're sick.

390
00:22:42.655 --> 00:22:43.685
Well...

391
00:22:44.314 --> 00:22:46.385
It looks like neither of us wants to say.

392
00:22:46.725 --> 00:22:48.185
I meant let's change the subject.

393
00:22:50.725 --> 00:22:51.764
Okay.

394
00:22:56.235 --> 00:22:57.635
What's the flower pot for?

395
00:22:59.635 --> 00:23:00.635
Oh. this?

396
00:23:01.705 --> 00:23:03.475
I'm waiting for it to bud.

397
00:23:03.475 --> 00:23:04.574
What did you plant?

398
00:23:06.175 --> 00:23:07.344
Well...

399
00:23:07.905 --> 00:23:09.114
I don't know...

400
00:23:09.544 --> 00:23:11.014
if it'll actually bud...

401
00:23:11.685 --> 00:23:13.344
and if it does. what it'll be.

402
00:23:17.915 --> 00:23:19.455
What if something strange grows?

403
00:23:19.685 --> 00:23:21.625
- I'll pull it out. - You'll pull it out?

404
00:23:22.455 --> 00:23:24.794
It's okay. I can just plant something else...

405
00:23:26.564 --> 00:23:27.695
since this is mine.

406
00:23:29.364 --> 00:23:31.034
That one isn't mine.

407
00:23:32.405 --> 00:23:33.435
but this one...

408
00:23:34.534 --> 00:23:35.604
is mine.

409
00:23:40.544 --> 00:23:42.544
I hope something good grows.

410
00:23:43.274 --> 00:23:45.014
I hope so too.

411
00:23:45.485 --> 00:23:47.344
I've put in a lot of effort. and I am waiting patiently...

412
00:23:47.915 --> 00:23:49.215
since it's my first time.

413
00:24:04.665 --> 00:24:06.735
I'm done drinking. so I'm going to go.

414
00:24:06.935 --> 00:24:09.074
What? Okay.

415
00:24:11.975 --> 00:24:14.705
Here's a gift since you opened my bottle for me.

416
00:24:23.715 --> 00:24:25.125
I'll be seeing you.

417
00:24:52.584 --> 00:24:54.385
(Tak Brother)

418
00:24:55.155 --> 00:24:56.185
Hey.

419
00:24:57.284 --> 00:24:58.385
Are you done?

420
00:24:59.685 --> 00:25:00.725
Okay.

421
00:25:01.155 --> 00:25:03.324
Why did they lock up...

422
00:25:03.324 --> 00:25:05.665
that crazy murderer in the hospital?

423
00:25:05.764 --> 00:25:09.064
I think the ghost is cursed.

424
00:25:10.264 --> 00:25:11.635
Maybe it's that ghost.

425
00:25:13.435 --> 00:25:15.405
- A ghost? - Yes.

426
00:25:16.274 --> 00:25:19.504
This rumor started a few years ago that there's a doctor...

427
00:25:19.875 --> 00:25:21.675
who's really a ghost.

428
00:25:22.145 --> 00:25:23.774
Lots of people saw him.

429
00:25:23.774 --> 00:25:26.514
But strangely. no one saw him twice.

430
00:25:26.514 --> 00:25:28.084
How scary.

431
00:25:28.814 --> 00:25:30.385
- What? - Why?

432
00:25:30.385 --> 00:25:32.024
I think I saw that ghost doctor.

433
00:25:32.324 --> 00:25:34.155
Last time. when I came to.

434
00:25:34.155 --> 00:25:36.895
I was bawling in front of a doctor for no reason.

435
00:25:37.455 --> 00:25:38.594
For the life of me.

436
00:25:38.594 --> 00:25:40.225
I couldn't remember why I was crying.

437
00:25:40.225 --> 00:25:41.895
It was weird. so I asked.

438
00:25:42.594 --> 00:25:45.205
and they said there was no such doctor.

439
00:25:46.564 --> 00:25:48.364
Then whom did I meet?

440
00:25:48.364 --> 00:25:50.635
He was about this tall. right?

441
00:25:51.405 --> 00:25:53.875
No. He was much taller.

442
00:25:53.875 --> 00:25:56.514
At least 190cm.

443
00:25:56.514 --> 00:25:59.215
Lady in the next room saw him too.

444
00:25:59.344 --> 00:26:01.985
She said he looked about 20 years old.

445
00:26:01.985 --> 00:26:03.854
No. He had gray hair.

446
00:26:04.084 --> 00:26:06.024
He was at least in his 50s.

447
00:26:06.524 --> 00:26:07.554
Excuse me.

448
00:26:07.554 --> 00:26:10.594
You said you saw that ghost too. didn't you?

449
00:26:10.594 --> 00:26:11.864
What did he look like?

450
00:26:12.125 --> 00:26:13.665
Was he this big...

451
00:26:13.665 --> 00:26:14.995
or this big?

452
00:26:14.995 --> 00:26:17.165
A young man in his 20s? Or an old man in his 50s?

453
00:26:18.465 --> 00:26:19.504
It was...

454
00:26:21.534 --> 00:26:22.804
a woman.

455
00:26:24.375 --> 00:26:26.574
- There is more than one. - Right.

456
00:26:27.175 --> 00:26:28.645
Switch hospitals.

457
00:26:28.645 --> 00:26:30.415
It's too late for us.

458
00:26:37.014 --> 00:26:38.415
Thank you. doctor.

459
00:26:38.985 --> 00:26:40.125
I'm sorry...

460
00:26:40.254 --> 00:26:42.695
for worrying you and wasting your time.

461
00:26:42.895 --> 00:26:46.364
A doctor is just trying to treat a patient.

462
00:26:46.364 --> 00:26:47.564
Why are you sorry?

463
00:26:48.165 --> 00:26:50.665
It's only natural for you to bug me about deadlines.

464
00:26:51.135 --> 00:26:53.205
It's only natural for me to do this.

465
00:26:54.735 --> 00:26:56.504
Since we're on the topic.

466
00:26:57.774 --> 00:27:00.405
you know the deadline is next week.

467
00:27:03.344 --> 00:27:05.314
You switch gears instantly...

468
00:27:05.485 --> 00:27:07.215
when you talk about work.

469
00:27:09.514 --> 00:27:10.554
Hi there.

470
00:27:11.614 --> 00:27:14.554
Hey. How did you know I was here?

471
00:27:16.495 --> 00:27:18.024
I brought flowers this time.

472
00:27:23.395 --> 00:27:25.334
You have another little brother?

473
00:27:27.534 --> 00:27:29.405
- Are you the youngest? - Him?

474
00:27:30.304 --> 00:27:31.375
No.

475
00:27:33.044 --> 00:27:34.304
Is he your boyfriend?

476
00:27:34.304 --> 00:27:36.014
He looks much younger than your brother...

477
00:27:36.514 --> 00:27:38.985
What? Boy... Boyfriend?

478
00:27:39.415 --> 00:27:41.485
He looks much younger... Hold on.

479
00:27:43.215 --> 00:27:45.824
My apologies. My apologies.

480
00:27:46.185 --> 00:27:48.225
I shouldn't have asked something so personal.

481
00:27:48.754 --> 00:27:51.054
Love breaks all boundaries.

482
00:27:51.354 --> 00:27:53.524
- Age is nothing. - What?

483
00:27:53.524 --> 00:27:55.195
Our age difference isn't that big.

484
00:27:55.965 --> 00:27:56.965
What?

485
00:27:58.604 --> 00:28:01.564
Have we met before?

486
00:28:03.034 --> 00:28:04.875
No. we haven't.

487
00:28:06.645 --> 00:28:07.675
Dong Kyung!

488
00:28:08.375 --> 00:28:09.375
Hey.

489
00:28:11.445 --> 00:28:13.145
- Big brother? - Big brother?

490
00:28:17.385 --> 00:28:19.455
Sure. that's right.

491
00:28:19.685 --> 00:28:21.925
Age doesn't matter when it comes to family hierarchies.

492
00:28:21.925 --> 00:28:25.324
I understand. I have an uncle who's younger than I am.

493
00:28:25.324 --> 00:28:27.294
He's only this big. but...

494
00:28:27.965 --> 00:28:29.165
Did you dye your hair?

495
00:28:29.695 --> 00:28:30.764
It looks good.

496
00:28:31.334 --> 00:28:33.564
It looks good against your skin tone.

497
00:28:34.304 --> 00:28:35.304
Hey.

498
00:28:35.975 --> 00:28:37.205
Did you dye your hair?

499
00:28:37.574 --> 00:28:39.044
That must be what he sees.

500
00:28:42.145 --> 00:28:43.975
Please get back safely.

501
00:28:43.975 --> 00:28:45.784
Call me if you need anything.

502
00:28:46.114 --> 00:28:48.344
I will. Thank you. doctor.

503
00:28:48.344 --> 00:28:49.514
Thank you. doctor.

504
00:28:58.625 --> 00:28:59.794
Let's take a picture.

505
00:28:59.794 --> 00:29:02.064
A picture? That's so random.

506
00:29:02.064 --> 00:29:03.895
To celebrate you getting flowers from him.

507
00:29:04.135 --> 00:29:06.405
Flowers? No...

508
00:29:06.405 --> 00:29:07.935
These are just...

509
00:29:07.935 --> 00:29:09.975
Aren't they from him? Did you find them?

510
00:29:10.175 --> 00:29:12.175
I did give them to her.

511
00:29:12.504 --> 00:29:13.645
See?

512
00:29:14.344 --> 00:29:16.514
Come on. Get in.

513
00:29:16.514 --> 00:29:18.014
1. 2. 3.

514
00:29:21.014 --> 00:29:23.054
See? It looks good.

515
00:29:24.614 --> 00:29:27.254
Hey. What's wrong with him? Why does he look like this?

516
00:29:27.254 --> 00:29:28.824
What? He came out nice.

517
00:29:29.995 --> 00:29:31.995
Do you think he looks much better in person?

518
00:29:32.324 --> 00:29:34.094
Give it a rest.

519
00:29:34.764 --> 00:29:35.834
It came out nice.

520
00:29:37.135 --> 00:29:38.334
Hey. how...

521
00:29:40.405 --> 00:29:41.764
He looks good.

522
00:29:42.375 --> 00:29:43.405
This is...

523
00:29:44.405 --> 00:29:45.574
Hey.

524
00:29:46.375 --> 00:29:49.645
I ran through a bunch of theories in my head...

525
00:29:51.675 --> 00:29:56.054
Does everyone see you differently?

526
00:29:56.584 --> 00:29:59.284
Sun Kyung says you dyed your hair.

527
00:29:59.284 --> 00:30:01.385
Mr. Jung asks if you're my youngest brother.

528
00:30:01.754 --> 00:30:03.925
I'm obviously much younger.

529
00:30:04.455 --> 00:30:06.695
I don't know about that last part.

530
00:30:07.824 --> 00:30:08.935
Am I right?

531
00:30:09.794 --> 00:30:11.034
Didn't I tell you?

532
00:30:11.034 --> 00:30:12.735
I'm right? For real?

533
00:30:13.034 --> 00:30:14.034
Wow.

534
00:30:14.034 --> 00:30:16.735
Then what I see may not be the real you...

535
00:30:16.735 --> 00:30:17.905
It is the real me.

536
00:30:20.574 --> 00:30:22.274
Only you can see the real me.

537
00:30:22.614 --> 00:30:23.774
It seems that way.

538
00:30:24.715 --> 00:30:27.314
- How? - That's why you're a weirdo.

539
00:30:28.385 --> 00:30:30.685
You can see the real me. call for me.

540
00:30:30.685 --> 00:30:31.715
and gave me a name.

541
00:30:35.955 --> 00:30:39.965
That's why you kept telling me to love you.

542
00:30:40.225 --> 00:30:42.635
You know. when someone can see you for who you really are.

543
00:30:42.635 --> 00:30:45.235
it makes your heart flutter. That's it. right?

544
00:30:49.334 --> 00:30:52.875
If you don't answer that. it makes me feel so awkward.

545
00:30:57.614 --> 00:30:59.415
Did I figure out your move? Is that it?

546
00:30:59.415 --> 00:31:02.155
Are you saying I'm the first woman to see the real you or something?

547
00:31:02.685 --> 00:31:04.754
It's true. You are the first person...

548
00:31:04.955 --> 00:31:06.284
that I ever interacted with in this way.

549
00:31:10.495 --> 00:31:12.925
Everything is a first to me.

550
00:31:18.334 --> 00:31:21.034
Is that so? I see.

551
00:31:21.504 --> 00:31:23.375
Okay. I see.

552
00:31:45.864 --> 00:31:48.225
Kim Human. stop!

553
00:31:52.705 --> 00:31:54.304
(Park Young)

554
00:31:54.435 --> 00:31:55.475
(Park Young)

555
00:31:58.334 --> 00:31:59.705
("Highteen Dream")

556
00:32:02.574 --> 00:32:05.814
Hey. You! Wait. Excuse me.

557
00:32:05.814 --> 00:32:07.814
Hey!

558
00:32:07.985 --> 00:32:10.584
Hey! Park Young!

559
00:32:11.155 --> 00:32:14.125
Park Young... Hey. Young Prince!

560
00:32:21.524 --> 00:32:23.864
Hey. What? What was that?

561
00:32:24.534 --> 00:32:27.564
Did you just look away? Our eyes just met!

562
00:32:27.564 --> 00:32:30.205
I know you just saw me! Hey!

563
00:32:30.875 --> 00:32:31.935
Hold on.

564
00:32:37.074 --> 00:32:39.344
What? Should I put you back in?

565
00:32:50.754 --> 00:32:51.794
("Highteen Dream")

566
00:32:51.794 --> 00:32:54.764
(Park Young: Vote for your actor!)

567
00:33:03.175 --> 00:33:04.235
(Don't find me.)

568
00:33:04.274 --> 00:33:06.544
Don't find me. I'll be at the dorm starting today.

569
00:33:06.774 --> 00:33:09.774
And phones aren't allowed here. so you can't reach me.

570
00:33:11.475 --> 00:33:14.084
And tell your friends about me.

571
00:33:14.084 --> 00:33:15.114
Thanks.

572
00:33:22.725 --> 00:33:25.864
Hey. can you make him get eliminated?

573
00:33:25.864 --> 00:33:26.965
Is that your wish?

574
00:33:29.465 --> 00:33:31.334
(The First Open Audition Program for the Male Lead)

575
00:33:31.935 --> 00:33:34.334
It's not a wish.

576
00:33:34.935 --> 00:33:38.334
Do you think you can get in there as a judge?

577
00:33:39.604 --> 00:33:41.104
I asked you if that's your wish.

578
00:33:41.145 --> 00:33:43.774
Come on. How can you be so calculative?

579
00:33:43.774 --> 00:33:46.814
We live together. You can just help me out this once.

580
00:33:51.014 --> 00:33:52.385
I'm being serious.

581
00:33:52.925 --> 00:33:54.485
I'm serious.

582
00:33:55.084 --> 00:33:57.895
Can't you turn into Park Chan Uk or Bong Joon Ho?

583
00:34:07.705 --> 00:34:09.705
Gosh. Darn it.

584
00:34:31.003 --> 00:34:33.572
How can a writer apply to an audition TV program?

585
00:34:33.572 --> 00:34:34.943
That's unheard of.

586
00:34:35.282 --> 00:34:37.183
What if he really becomes the male lead?

587
00:34:37.183 --> 00:34:38.353
He might win.

588
00:34:38.353 --> 00:34:39.882
He has the most votes right now.

589
00:34:39.882 --> 00:34:41.652
He is the most handsome one there.

590
00:34:41.652 --> 00:34:43.452
You just sounded like a judge.

591
00:34:44.083 --> 00:34:46.253
If I were younger. I would have applied.

592
00:34:47.822 --> 00:34:51.023
"My wish is to make a debut."

593
00:34:51.862 --> 00:34:53.393
Wasn't that pretty good?

594
00:34:55.603 --> 00:34:58.972
Since we're talking about our wishes.

595
00:34:59.202 --> 00:35:00.202
what would you wish for...

596
00:35:00.202 --> 00:35:02.242
if you could make one wish before dying?

597
00:35:03.643 --> 00:35:05.172
But you can't make a wish to save your life.

598
00:35:05.172 --> 00:35:07.643
And you can't ask for multiple wishes. What would you wish for?

599
00:35:07.643 --> 00:35:09.112
- Money. - Money.

600
00:35:10.413 --> 00:35:12.083
- Fame. - "Fame"?

601
00:35:13.452 --> 00:35:16.782
What if you could only live for...

602
00:35:16.782 --> 00:35:17.952
Yes.

603
00:35:18.222 --> 00:35:20.322
Yes. hello. Hello?

604
00:35:21.523 --> 00:35:22.623
Hey...

605
00:35:23.492 --> 00:35:25.933
Yes. Really?

606
00:35:26.663 --> 00:35:27.862
Of course.

607
00:35:28.302 --> 00:35:31.003
Okay. Thanks.

608
00:35:33.132 --> 00:35:35.773
- What did you say? - Forget it.

609
00:35:35.773 --> 00:35:38.103
You are getting seasonal mood swings.

610
00:35:38.373 --> 00:35:40.043
Hey. don't worry.

611
00:35:40.043 --> 00:35:41.842
I'll make your wish come true.

612
00:35:43.543 --> 00:35:44.612
My wish?

613
00:35:45.213 --> 00:35:47.083
That was a call for your blind date.

614
00:35:47.512 --> 00:35:50.222
I set up what you asked for the other day.

615
00:35:50.422 --> 00:35:52.992
You can go after work later today. It's set up.

616
00:35:53.293 --> 00:35:55.722
- What? - "What"? What's that reaction?

617
00:35:55.722 --> 00:35:57.623
You can't pull out now.

618
00:35:58.733 --> 00:36:00.393
Ms. Jo. I was...

619
00:36:00.393 --> 00:36:02.663
You are putting me in a tight spot.

620
00:36:06.103 --> 00:36:07.202
A blind date?

621
00:36:09.572 --> 00:36:11.103
He's been friends with my boyfriend for 10 years.

622
00:36:11.103 --> 00:36:12.612
He's a really nice guy.

623
00:36:12.612 --> 00:36:15.612
I asked you to set me up with a guy you want to get rid of.

624
00:36:15.612 --> 00:36:16.782
Gosh.

625
00:36:16.782 --> 00:36:19.913
If this works out. you'll want to get rid of him someday.

626
00:36:25.693 --> 00:36:27.023
Sweetie.

627
00:36:29.092 --> 00:36:30.362
It's this again?

628
00:36:30.362 --> 00:36:31.523
Sweetie.

629
00:36:33.233 --> 00:36:35.333
Gosh. This is new.

630
00:36:38.032 --> 00:36:39.032
Hello.

631
00:36:40.873 --> 00:36:43.072
Sweetie. open your mouth.

632
00:36:44.842 --> 00:36:47.512
You always feed me when there are a lot of people.

633
00:36:50.643 --> 00:36:52.913
Dong Kyung. what do you do after work?

634
00:36:54.052 --> 00:36:57.052
I read books at home.

635
00:37:00.353 --> 00:37:02.822
What about you? What do you do after work?

636
00:37:02.822 --> 00:37:06.963
I don't do much because I have a pretty boring life.

637
00:37:07.032 --> 00:37:09.032
I just work out a bit.

638
00:37:10.302 --> 00:37:11.972
What kind of exercise do you do?

639
00:37:11.972 --> 00:37:12.972
Do you like working out?

640
00:37:12.972 --> 00:37:14.532
Yes. I do.

641
00:37:14.532 --> 00:37:17.603
As if. I've never seen you in sneakers.

642
00:37:18.972 --> 00:37:20.612
- What? - It's getting cold.

643
00:37:20.612 --> 00:37:21.913
So don't work out too hard.

644
00:37:22.282 --> 00:37:23.713
You'll get hurt.

645
00:37:38.063 --> 00:37:39.963
Since it's getting cold. do you want to stay indoors?

646
00:37:39.963 --> 00:37:42.262
Do you want to watch a movie next time? Do you like movies?

647
00:37:42.262 --> 00:37:44.532
Yes. I love movies.

648
00:37:44.532 --> 00:37:46.902
He's dying to see his end.

649
00:37:47.733 --> 00:37:48.773
What?

650
00:37:50.643 --> 00:37:53.612
Are you trying to die. sweetie?

651
00:37:53.873 --> 00:37:56.842
If you keep drinking like that. you'll get drunk.

652
00:38:00.012 --> 00:38:01.382
What? What's wrong with her?

653
00:38:01.853 --> 00:38:03.583
Ye Ji. Ye Ji!

654
00:38:03.583 --> 00:38:04.683
She's drunk.

655
00:38:05.452 --> 00:38:06.822
- What... - Is she okay?

656
00:38:06.822 --> 00:38:09.193
You should go home now. Gosh.

657
00:38:09.193 --> 00:38:10.523
She looks pretty drunk.

658
00:38:10.523 --> 00:38:11.762
And you don't think you are?

659
00:38:15.362 --> 00:38:17.202
What was that again?

660
00:38:19.503 --> 00:38:20.532
Let's go.

661
00:38:22.842 --> 00:38:26.242
I mean... How can I leave when they are so drunk?

662
00:38:26.242 --> 00:38:27.512
They'll wake up in five minutes.

663
00:38:28.882 --> 00:38:31.012
Hey. hold on. But still. Wait.

664
00:38:31.012 --> 00:38:32.552
They won't remember a thing anyway.

665
00:38:33.112 --> 00:38:35.183
Hey. Okay. Fine. Wait.

666
00:38:36.382 --> 00:38:37.552
Ye Ji...

667
00:38:41.123 --> 00:38:43.592
Hey. just because you have the powers.

668
00:38:43.592 --> 00:38:46.132
you can't do something like that just as you please. If you do...

669
00:38:46.132 --> 00:38:47.163
Then. what?

670
00:38:48.433 --> 00:38:49.702
Is that too mean?

671
00:38:50.233 --> 00:38:51.302
What?

672
00:38:51.972 --> 00:38:52.972
That's good.

673
00:38:53.302 --> 00:38:55.773
If you're looking for a bad guy who will die in place of you.

674
00:38:56.072 --> 00:38:58.373
I'm the perfect candidate.

675
00:39:00.072 --> 00:39:03.382
Is that why you came to my date today to show me that?

676
00:39:08.382 --> 00:39:11.183
I have a good idea about your wish.

677
00:39:15.322 --> 00:39:17.963
Make a wish to fall in love with me.

678
00:39:20.233 --> 00:39:21.663
Are you saying that's possible?

679
00:39:22.603 --> 00:39:23.802
Why wouldn't it be?

680
00:40:07.727 --> 00:40:08.767
See? It's possible.

681
00:40:18.036 --> 00:40:19.337
What's your type?

682
00:40:19.937 --> 00:40:20.977
That's quite sudden.

683
00:40:20.977 --> 00:40:22.747
It'll help me come up with the male protagonist.

684
00:40:23.377 --> 00:40:24.747
I kind of already know.

685
00:40:24.946 --> 00:40:26.647
but I just need to double-check.

686
00:40:30.017 --> 00:40:32.087
- A good-looking man. - That's a given.

687
00:40:32.817 --> 00:40:35.056
No one wants an ugly male protagonist in a romance novel.

688
00:40:36.826 --> 00:40:38.797
- Then... - He'll be handsome for sure.

689
00:40:38.797 --> 00:40:41.056
but he needs to have the ability to make a girl's heart flutter.

690
00:40:41.256 --> 00:40:42.797
That's exactly why people get bored...

691
00:40:42.797 --> 00:40:44.727
of your typical male protagonists. They're just good-looking.

692
00:40:44.727 --> 00:40:46.997
Do you know how hard it is just to be good-looking?

693
00:40:46.997 --> 00:40:49.866
We always suffer having to hire the right illustrator for you.

694
00:40:51.267 --> 00:40:53.636
Do you really think you're the one who completes the guy's looks?

695
00:40:55.877 --> 00:40:56.946
Whatever.

696
00:40:58.207 --> 00:40:59.446
A charming male protagonist is great.

697
00:41:00.147 --> 00:41:02.547
But you need to think about what it is that makes...

698
00:41:02.547 --> 00:41:03.647
the handsome guy so charming.

699
00:41:04.147 --> 00:41:06.056
Is he rich or competent?

700
00:41:06.357 --> 00:41:08.826
What is the one crucial thing that he lacks?

701
00:41:09.656 --> 00:41:11.627
So the female protagonist can fill up what he lacks?

702
00:41:11.627 --> 00:41:12.957
Now we're talking.

703
00:41:23.866 --> 00:41:25.806
But don't you think we're going too fast?

704
00:41:26.736 --> 00:41:27.777
What do you mean?

705
00:41:28.277 --> 00:41:30.147
We're together at my house late at night.

706
00:41:30.547 --> 00:41:31.747
This is too fast.

707
00:41:32.877 --> 00:41:35.386
We have no other choice. I have to go to work.

708
00:41:36.116 --> 00:41:38.247
Plus. you prefer to work late at night.

709
00:41:39.457 --> 00:41:41.286
Yes. you're right.

710
00:42:08.986 --> 00:42:10.346
It's been bothering me for a while.

711
00:42:15.556 --> 00:42:16.556
What?

712
00:42:17.227 --> 00:42:18.527
Did that make your heart flutter?

713
00:42:19.627 --> 00:42:20.627
No.

714
00:42:26.696 --> 00:42:28.136
We should call it a day.

715
00:42:33.437 --> 00:42:34.837
Joo Ik. I'm off now.

716
00:42:35.236 --> 00:42:36.676
Thanks for lending me your car.

717
00:42:37.306 --> 00:42:38.917
Sure. Let's call it a day.

718
00:42:39.216 --> 00:42:40.576
It seems like you have somewhere to go.

719
00:42:44.986 --> 00:42:47.216
- When is our next meeting? - I'll call you.

720
00:43:08.207 --> 00:43:10.176
I guess you don't easily throw things away.

721
00:43:11.346 --> 00:43:12.377
What?

722
00:43:18.647 --> 00:43:20.716
- I'm going to take this. - Is it raining?

723
00:43:25.696 --> 00:43:28.027
No. it's not. But this is mine.

724
00:43:34.297 --> 00:43:35.736
Gosh. how embarrassing.

725
00:43:36.437 --> 00:43:38.167
Why did I put that there?

726
00:43:41.676 --> 00:43:42.747
Darn it.

727
00:43:56.468 --> 00:43:57.499
Gosh.

728
00:44:08.294 --> 00:44:10.194
Why am I the only girl?

729
00:44:10.194 --> 00:44:11.464
I called all the other girls.

730
00:44:11.464 --> 00:44:12.763
but they suddenly canceled last minute.

731
00:44:13.203 --> 00:44:14.734
I didn't know this was going to happen.

732
00:44:14.734 --> 00:44:16.103
They all have boyfriends.

733
00:44:16.103 --> 00:44:17.703
What kind of guy would let their girlfriend...

734
00:44:17.834 --> 00:44:20.603
attend a school reunion where it's mostly men?

735
00:44:20.603 --> 00:44:21.703
Gosh. this is sad.

736
00:44:21.703 --> 00:44:23.674
"Men"? You guys aren't men.

737
00:44:23.674 --> 00:44:24.814
Of course. we're men.

738
00:44:24.814 --> 00:44:28.413
But I must say. Ji Na is just as pretty as she used to be.

739
00:44:29.053 --> 00:44:30.254
Are you seeing anyone?

740
00:44:30.584 --> 00:44:33.123
You guys are just as ugly as before.

741
00:44:33.683 --> 00:44:35.484
What do you care whether or not I'm seeing anyone?

742
00:44:35.484 --> 00:44:37.424
Gosh. she still has a nasty temper.

743
00:44:38.123 --> 00:44:39.464
You must be upset that Hyun Kyu isn't here.

744
00:44:39.464 --> 00:44:40.623
I bet you came to see him.

745
00:44:42.594 --> 00:44:44.064
I'm not here to see him.

746
00:44:44.234 --> 00:44:45.594
I came to eat chicken.

747
00:44:46.303 --> 00:44:47.303
As if...

748
00:44:47.303 --> 00:44:48.404
I thought he was coming.

749
00:44:49.373 --> 00:44:50.433
He told me he'd be here.

750
00:44:50.433 --> 00:44:51.504
- Really? - Yes.

751
00:44:51.504 --> 00:44:52.643
He never contacted me.

752
00:44:54.873 --> 00:44:56.073
I'm sure he'll show up.

753
00:45:05.654 --> 00:45:06.754
Hey. Hyun Kyu.

754
00:45:06.754 --> 00:45:08.424
- Hey. - Hey.

755
00:45:08.424 --> 00:45:10.594
- Get over here. - Look at you.

756
00:45:10.594 --> 00:45:12.294
You guys haven't changed at all.

757
00:45:12.294 --> 00:45:14.194
- Same goes for you. - Come over here.

758
00:45:17.033 --> 00:45:18.594
There was no parking space nearby.

759
00:45:18.594 --> 00:45:20.364
So I had to drive around.

760
00:45:20.364 --> 00:45:22.973
But it looks like you found space right outside the restaurant.

761
00:45:23.174 --> 00:45:25.573
- Nice car. - You must be doing well.

762
00:45:26.044 --> 00:45:27.073
No. that's nonsense.

763
00:45:28.643 --> 00:45:30.913
- Are you drunk? - What's your car?

764
00:45:31.214 --> 00:45:32.373
I don't have a car.

765
00:45:33.844 --> 00:45:34.944
- You don't? - No.

766
00:45:36.084 --> 00:45:38.183
- How are things going? - You look great.

767
00:45:38.183 --> 00:45:40.823
Me? I've always looked great.

768
00:45:40.823 --> 00:45:43.154
This guy hasn't aged at all.

769
00:45:43.154 --> 00:45:45.194
What are you talking about?

770
00:45:45.194 --> 00:45:46.864
Let's be honest. It was your fault.

771
00:45:46.864 --> 00:45:49.024
- Cheers. - Cut it out.

772
00:45:49.594 --> 00:45:51.663
Hyun Kyu. do you still hate rice cakes?

773
00:45:52.294 --> 00:45:53.364
Rice cakes?

774
00:45:53.964 --> 00:45:56.103
What do you mean? I don't hate rice cakes.

775
00:45:57.103 --> 00:45:59.143
Oh. right. Was it Ji Na who didn't eat rice cakes?

776
00:45:59.143 --> 00:46:01.174
Yes. I don't eat rice cakes.

777
00:46:03.573 --> 00:46:04.774
I hate them.

778
00:46:07.013 --> 00:46:08.314
Hey. hey.

779
00:46:08.884 --> 00:46:10.884
Hyun Kyu eats rice cakes even though they gave him an upset stomach...

780
00:46:10.884 --> 00:46:12.484
and made him fail his CSATs.

781
00:46:12.823 --> 00:46:15.084
But Ji Na hates them because that made him go study abroad.

782
00:46:15.084 --> 00:46:17.294
which was what led them to break up.

783
00:46:18.194 --> 00:46:19.364
Wait a minute.

784
00:46:19.924 --> 00:46:22.123
Do you still have feelings for Hyun Kyu?

785
00:46:28.634 --> 00:46:30.634
- That's nonsense. - Gosh. let's just drink.

786
00:46:30.634 --> 00:46:32.844
- Let's just drink. - Cheers.

787
00:46:32.844 --> 00:46:34.073
Drink up.

788
00:46:34.073 --> 00:46:36.373
- It's nice to see you. - You too.

789
00:46:36.873 --> 00:46:39.013
Hey. Have you heard of the news?

790
00:46:56.094 --> 00:46:57.134
Are you okay?

791
00:46:58.134 --> 00:46:59.334
You drank a lot today.

792
00:47:03.603 --> 00:47:04.774
Are you drunk?

793
00:47:05.203 --> 00:47:07.544
No. I don't get drunk that easily.

794
00:47:07.544 --> 00:47:08.643
I can hold my liquor.

795
00:47:09.243 --> 00:47:10.243
Really?

796
00:47:11.814 --> 00:47:12.884
That's good to hear.

797
00:47:15.544 --> 00:47:18.084
- Why are you here? - I was worried about you.

798
00:47:21.223 --> 00:47:22.553
No. why are you here?

799
00:47:24.094 --> 00:47:26.464
Why are you back in Korea. and why did you come to the reunion?

800
00:47:30.234 --> 00:47:32.033
Forget it. Just go.

801
00:47:35.134 --> 00:47:36.303
Should I take you home?

802
00:47:42.544 --> 00:47:44.274
It's okay. Just go.

803
00:47:47.783 --> 00:47:48.913
Here's a cab.

804
00:47:55.123 --> 00:47:56.154
I'll see you.

805
00:48:50.643 --> 00:48:53.314
- Hey. - Hey. You were home.

806
00:49:14.203 --> 00:49:15.364
That's right.

807
00:49:17.303 --> 00:49:18.373
Thanks for the car.

808
00:49:19.803 --> 00:49:20.873
Sure.

809
00:49:22.873 --> 00:49:23.913
What about your first love?

810
00:49:26.844 --> 00:49:29.584
- What? - How did it go?

811
00:49:32.013 --> 00:49:33.584
It was...

812
00:50:15.123 --> 00:50:16.794
We're late. Let's go.

813
00:51:23.241 --> 00:51:25.281
I can wish for that?

814
00:51:25.811 --> 00:51:28.210
How could that work?

815
00:51:29.351 --> 00:51:31.820
Make a wish to fall in love with me.

816
00:51:33.020 --> 00:51:35.491
But I can't wish for that.

817
00:51:36.291 --> 00:51:38.090
What does he take me for?

818
00:51:38.520 --> 00:51:40.391
Talk to yourself when you're alone.

819
00:51:41.360 --> 00:51:42.391
Sir.

820
00:51:43.601 --> 00:51:45.031
I shouldn't have said anything.

821
00:51:45.561 --> 00:51:46.630
What?

822
00:51:47.531 --> 00:51:51.500
If you could wish for anything. what would you wish for?

823
00:51:51.500 --> 00:51:52.570
The lottery.

824
00:51:53.110 --> 00:51:55.011
That was automatic.

825
00:51:55.011 --> 00:51:56.610
You must wish for that all the time.

826
00:51:56.610 --> 00:51:58.480
Everyone wishes for that.

827
00:51:59.110 --> 00:52:01.411
What if you only had 100 days left to live?

828
00:52:01.411 --> 00:52:03.250
- Would you still wish for that? - That's silly.

829
00:52:03.480 --> 00:52:05.621
I'd wish to live longer.

830
00:52:06.491 --> 00:52:07.920
You can't wish for that.

831
00:52:09.491 --> 00:52:12.161
Is the person granting your wish good-looking?

832
00:52:12.561 --> 00:52:14.590
Yes. he is a bit...

833
00:52:14.590 --> 00:52:16.331
What? How did you know it was a guy?

834
00:52:16.331 --> 00:52:20.070
No. that he's good-looking... No. that...

835
00:52:20.070 --> 00:52:21.070
It's obvious.

836
00:52:21.230 --> 00:52:23.440
What main character in a romance novel isn't handsome?

837
00:52:24.570 --> 00:52:25.701
Whose story is it?

838
00:52:26.070 --> 00:52:29.781
Well. so... It's a new writer.

839
00:52:30.411 --> 00:52:31.811
You wouldn't know.

840
00:52:31.940 --> 00:52:34.480
Then you should wish for a passionate relationship with him.

841
00:52:35.610 --> 00:52:38.320
- What? - Isn't that how all romances start?

842
00:52:39.250 --> 00:52:40.291
Seriously.

843
00:52:42.391 --> 00:52:44.721
"Let me truly love you."

844
00:52:44.721 --> 00:52:46.630
Is that the correct wish?

845
00:52:47.090 --> 00:52:49.831
Seriously. Is that the only way?

846
00:52:50.561 --> 00:52:51.730
What are you talking about?

847
00:52:52.761 --> 00:52:53.900
It's the opposite.

848
00:52:55.770 --> 00:52:58.601
Not me. "Make you fall in love with me."

849
00:52:58.601 --> 00:52:59.911
"Crazy in love."

850
00:53:08.351 --> 00:53:09.581
Crazy...

851
00:53:11.221 --> 00:53:12.281
in love.

852
00:53:53.991 --> 00:53:55.431
What are you doing here?

853
00:53:56.431 --> 00:53:58.701
I was hiding from the rain.

854
00:54:00.270 --> 00:54:01.770
What was I expecting?

855
00:54:02.570 --> 00:54:03.900
Did you expect something?

856
00:54:05.940 --> 00:54:07.170
Don't you have an umbrella?

857
00:54:09.541 --> 00:54:11.340
I wouldn't be standing here if I did.

858
00:54:12.411 --> 00:54:14.880
- I don't either. - I know.

859
00:54:24.391 --> 00:54:27.261
Why does it always rain in my life?

860
00:54:27.690 --> 00:54:29.800
And why don't I ever have an umbrella?

861
00:54:37.541 --> 00:54:38.601
Shall we run?

862
00:54:39.141 --> 00:54:40.141
What?

863
00:54:46.781 --> 00:54:49.011
Hey. Hey. Hey!

864
00:54:56.491 --> 00:54:58.860
Hey. Can't you stop the rain?

865
00:54:58.860 --> 00:55:01.161
- I can. - Then why are we running?

866
00:55:01.561 --> 00:55:03.300
- It's fun. - What?

867
00:55:03.400 --> 00:55:05.661
Stop it! Stop. Let go.

868
00:55:05.931 --> 00:55:07.101
Seriously.

869
00:55:07.331 --> 00:55:10.000
Look at me. I'm soaked.

870
00:55:10.371 --> 00:55:13.270
It would be better to just walk.

871
00:55:13.340 --> 00:55:14.911
That's less tiring.

872
00:55:16.411 --> 00:55:17.681
Are you still tired?

873
00:55:20.610 --> 00:55:21.911
I'm okay now.

874
00:55:23.880 --> 00:55:25.650
I can finally breathe.

875
00:55:26.920 --> 00:55:27.991
See?

876
00:55:29.791 --> 00:55:31.020
The rain isn't a big deal.

877
00:55:33.230 --> 00:55:35.161
Even if you're the only one without an umbrella. it's fine.

878
00:55:35.690 --> 00:55:38.460
Just get wet. Get wet and run.

879
00:55:41.300 --> 00:55:42.500
You'll be home soon.

880
00:55:57.980 --> 00:55:59.181
I have a wish.

881
00:56:03.520 --> 00:56:04.590
I want you...

882
00:56:06.190 --> 00:56:08.261
to love me.

883
00:56:12.431 --> 00:56:16.031
Can I wish for that too?

884
00:56:20.210 --> 00:56:21.270
No.

885
00:57:19.161 --> 00:57:21.431
If something messes up the system.

886
00:57:21.670 --> 00:57:24.170
it means it was programmed wrong.

887
00:57:26.411 --> 00:57:27.710
Something that is wrong...

888
00:57:29.270 --> 00:57:30.681
must be deleted.

889
00:58:15.221 --> 00:58:16.250
What is it?

890
00:58:22.331 --> 00:58:23.360
Or...

891
00:58:25.101 --> 00:58:26.300
it should be reset.

892
00:59:16.041 --> 00:59:19.981
(Doom at Your Service)

893
00:59:21.094 --> 00:59:23.965
People who are nice always disappear.

894
00:59:25.695 --> 00:59:27.065
- You're responsible for... - Hello?

895
00:59:27.065 --> 00:59:28.835
- everything that disappears. - Stop!

896
00:59:29.905 --> 00:59:32.605
Let me drive you home. I'm worried.

897
00:59:33.344 --> 00:59:35.405
Did you know Dong Kyung was sick?

898
00:59:36.005 --> 00:59:39.715
So you want to be loved by her. That's it. right?

899
00:59:39.985 --> 00:59:41.514
That was a wrong conclusion.

900
00:59:42.184 --> 00:59:44.385
What do you mean by that?

901
00:59:44.914 --> 00:59:47.684
You are miserable because I exist.

902
00:59:48.155 --> 00:59:50.795
So you should choose yourself and the world.

902
00:59:51.305 --> 01:00:51.641
